  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_11",
    "text": "\"A restaurant's fish order is not taking the subway from the Bronx to Midtown Manhat- tan,\" said Andrew Rigie, execu- tive director of New York City Hospitality Alliance, which represents restaurants, bars and nightclubs.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5047801147227533,
      0.28105355295615503,
      0.6577437858508605,
      0.3326171719583035
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 13
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_17",
    "text": "Carriers say they already have plenty of incentives to deliver overnight.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8323773103887827,
      0.30078777751253283,
      0.9853409815168898,
      0.3195671202355375
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 14
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_15",
    "text": "Luciani said that because of traffic, A. Duie Pyle's drivers there average eight deliveries and pickups a day, compared with an average of 23 daily de- liveries and pickups across the wider region. He said average toll costs per delivery are al- most three times higher in the city than regionwide.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6692160611854685,
      0.3132012413463834,
      0.8215423836838751,
      0.37845149996021327
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 15
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_9",
    "text": "Continued from page B1 Miller said trucking compa- nies will absorb some of the ex- tra costs from the tolls, but they will have to pass on a portion of the fees to customers such as restaurants and bars that al- ready operate on thin margins. \" have heard a lot of conce about losing customers because of increased rates.\" he said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3403441682600382,
      0.3147927110686719,
      0.4926704907584449,
      0.38258932123816347
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 16
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_19",
    "text": "Traffic is lighter and curb space is available. But they say many customers can't ac- cept overnight deliveries be- cause they don't have over- night staff or a secure location for unattended deliveries. \"' ust another tax and an other cost of doing business in the Big Apple,\" Luciani said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8304652644996813,
      0.3202037081244529,
      0.9853409815168898,
      0.384180790960452
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 17
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_12",
    "text": "\"That truck has to come into the zone and our suppliers have told us this is going to in- crease their cost of doing busi- ness,\" Rigie said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5047801147227533,
      0.3329354659027612,
      0.6577437858508605,
      0.36412827245961643
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 18
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_13",
    "text": "About 120,000 trucks and commercial vehicles enter the city each day, according to the city transportation department. John Luciani, an executive at A. Duie Pyle, a West Chester, Pa.-based trucking company fo- cused on the Northeast that consolidates shipments from multiple customers in a single trailer, says New York City is al- ready the most difficult and ex- naneive ritr it nneratac in",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5041427660930529,
      0.36444656640407413,
      0.6577437858508605,
      0.3838624970159943
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 19
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_16",
    "text": "\"The cost of doing business",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6730401529636711,
      0.37654173629346704,
      0.8215423836838751,
      0.3838624970159943
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 20
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_57",
    "text": "GFL Environmental to Sell Services Business In $5.6 Billion Deal",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.6679413639260675,
      0.39532107901647173,
      0.9802421924792861,
      0.4510225192965704
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 21
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_20",
    "text": "Law Firms Prepare for Trump",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.01338432122370937,
      0.39595766690538714,
      0.15360101975780752,
      0.4522956950744012
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 22
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_46",
    "text": "Trump and his allies, after years in which firms weren't shy about speaking out on is- sues including abortion rights, racial justice and the war in the Middle East.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5035054174633524,
      0.39595766690538714,
      0.6583811344805609,
      0.43447123418476963
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 23
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_28",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "picture",
    "bbox": [
      0.17654557042702357,
      0.39723084268321796,
      0.4933078393881453,
      0.5471472905227978
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 24
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_48",
    "text": "\"Tey ae re sensitiv this now than they have been in the past,\" said law firm consultant Peter Zeughauser. \"They are more careful.\"",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5035054174633524,
      0.43478952812922733,
      0.6577437858508605,
      0.466618922574998
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 25
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_21",
    "text": "Continued from page B1 trade adviser.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012109623964308477,
      0.45993474974138615,
      0.13193116634799235,
      0.4726665075196944
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 26
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_58",
    "text": "BY DENNY JACOB",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6673040152963671,
      0.45993474974138615,
      0.7463352453792225,
      0.466618922574998
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 27
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_60",
    "text": "pected to close in the first quar- ter.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8317399617590823,
      0.45993474974138615,
      0.9853409815168898,
      0.4726665075196944
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 28
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_47",
    "text": "Four years ago, some firms sought to distance themselves from Trump after he sought to overturn Joe Biden's 2020 electoral victory. The posi- tioning across the industry is far different now, and former Trump officials have become highly prized assets.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5022307202039515,
      0.4663006286305403,
      0.6583811344805609,
      0.5232752446884698
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 29
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_59",
    "text": "GFL Environmental has reached an agreement to sell its environmental services busi- ness in a deal valued at 8 billion Canadian dollars, equivalent to about $5.59 billion, though it would retain an equity interest. The Canadian company, which transports and recycles waste, among other services, said it reached the agreement with funds managed by affili- ates of Apollo and BC Partners. It would retain a 44% equity in- terest in the business, while funds managed by affiliates of Apollo and BC each would hold a 28% equity interest.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6679413639260675,
      0.4717116256863213,
      0.8221797323135756,
      0.5872523275244689
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 30
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_22",
    "text": "Top firms across the U.S. are also bracing for major changes in the antitrust land- scape. President Biden ap- pointed officials,including Federal Trade Commission Chair Lina Khan, who sought to increase enforcement to levels not seen in decades. That created a lucrative envi- ronment for antitrust lawyers as companies struggled to se- cure government clearance for a range of proposed merg- ers and acquisitions.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.47298480146415217,
      0.16507329509241556,
      0.5681546908570064
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 31
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_61",
    "text": "GFL expects cash proceeds from the deal to be around C$6.2 billion. It intends to use up to C$3.75 billion of the net proceeds to repay debt, leaving up to C$2.25 billion for share repurchases. The balance will go to transaction fees and gen- eral corporate purposes.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8323773103887827,
      0.47298480146415217,
      0.9853409815168898,
      0.5296411235776239
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 32
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_49",
    "text": "\"Firms are peacocking their Trump feathers in a way we haven't seen in recent memory,\" said Dan Binstock, a legal recruiter based in Wash- ington.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5035054174633524,
      0.524230126521843,
      0.6577437858508605,
      0.5617888119678524
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 33
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_62",
    "text": "Chief Executive Patrick Dovigi said a deleveraged bal- ance sheet will provide GFL with more financial flexibility to deploy capital into organic growth initiatives and solid waste M&A and allow for a greater return of capital to shareholders.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8317399617590823,
      0.5299594175220816,
      0.9853409815168898,
      0.5869340335800112
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 34
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_29",
    "text": "Coinbase CEo Brian Armstrong said his company wouldn't work with any firm that hires certain Biden-era regulators.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17590822179732313,
      0.5490570541895441,
      0.4805608667941364,
      0.5621071059123101
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 35
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_50",
    "text": "Among the firms eager to champion its D.C. ties is Akin, which has been pitching itself as particularly well placed for the coming administration. Its marketing tools include a new biweekly policy publication on how clients can navigate the nnctalantion landenana",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5041427660930529,
      0.5621071059123101,
      0.6590184831102613,
      0.6165353704145778
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 36
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_33",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17718291905672404,
      0.5681546908570064,
      0.32887189292543023,
      0.5872523275244689
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 37
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_23",
    "text": "Trump's new administra- tion likely means a more hands-off approach, which in some ways could reduce the windfall for antitrust litiga- tors and counselors. But the more predictable and favor- able regulatory climate, along with economic factors, could drive new corporate dealmak- ing and provide a healthy stream of legal revenue.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.5684729848014641,
      0.16443594646271512,
      0.644545237526856
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 38
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_37",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3403441682600382,
      0.5684729848014641,
      0.4926704907584449,
      0.5999840853027771
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 39
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_63",
    "text": "GFL said its board, when ex- cluding interested directors who have recused themselves, has unanimously approved the transaction. The deal is ex-",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6704907584448694,
      0.5875706214689266,
      0.8202676864244742,
      0.6190817219702395
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 40
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_64",
    "text": "Dovigi said the company will maintain an option to repur- chase the environmental ser- vices business within five years of closing.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8323773103887827,
      0.5875706214689266,
      0.9847036328871893,
      0.6194000159146972
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 41
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_30",
    "text": "The firm is now marketing the practice anew after the divisiveness of the 2024 elec- tion and a backlash against some policies embraced by progressives. The group helps employers \"lower the temper- ature\" around hot-button so- cial and political issues, Almon said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17654557042702357,
      0.5878889154133843,
      0.32887189292543023,
      0.6499562345826371
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 42
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_38",
    "text": "Firms themselves also face political challenges. One early example came in December, when Coinbase CEO Brian Armstrong said his company wouldn't work with anyone who hires Biden-era officials who were part of the adminis- tration's ag- gressive en- fo r c e m e n t efforts against crypto compa- nies. And he singled out law firm Milbank by name for hiring the Se- curities and",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3403441682600382,
      0.6003023792472348,
      0.4926704907584449,
      0.6505928224715525
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 43
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_39",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.397068196303378,
      0.6025304368584388,
      0.4933078393881453,
      0.7308028964748946
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 44
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_51",
    "text": "The firm's roster of D.C. in- siders includes former Rep. Kevin Brady, who as Republi- can chair of the House Ways and Means Committee during the first Trump administra- tion helped usher in a sweep- ing package of tax cuts—many of which are set to expire at the end of this year.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5041427660930529,
      0.6178085461924087,
      0.6583811344805609,
      0.6824222169173232
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 45
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_65",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "picture",
    "bbox": [
      0.668578712555768,
      0.6318134797485477,
      0.9891650732950924,
      0.7441712421421183
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 46
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_24",
    "text": "Ropes & Gray antitrust partner Jonathan Klarfeld said he expects his practice area to return to a normal baseline after years of drawn- out enforcement built on pro- gressive and untested legal theories.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.644545237526856,
      0.16379859783301465,
      0.6954722686400892
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 47
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_34",
    "text": "Law firm Gibson Dunn has built a spe- cialty out of counseling companies that have imple- mented policies and programs designed to promote diver- sity and inclu-",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17718291905672404,
      0.6515477043049256,
      0.25748884639898023,
      0.7276199570303175
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 48
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_35",
    "text": "Top firms are bracing for major changes in the antitrust landscape.",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.2734225621414914,
      0.6582318771385375,
      0.3964308476736775,
      0.7097954961406859
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 49
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_52",
    "text": "\"we have a pulse on all things Washington,\" said Abid Qureshi, Akin's co-chair-elect. Even before the election, top firms were engaged in a poaching war for star part- ners with expertise that could bring in new portfolios of business. Trump's victory— and the policy upheavals that come with it—only adds to that pressure.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5035054174633524,
      0.6827405108617809,
      0.6590184831102613,
      0.7594493514760882
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 50
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_25",
    "text": "\"Some of the excesses of recent enforcement are likely to be pared back,\" Klarfeld said, but added, '\"There is more than enough work to oc- cupy our time.\"",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012109623964308477,
      0.6961088565290046,
      0.16443594646271512,
      0.7336675419750139
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 51
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_36",
    "text": "Exchange Commission's re- cent enforcement director. \"Let your law firms know that hiring these folks means losing you as a client,\" Arm- strong wrote on X. Milbank didn't respond to a request for comment. More broadly, law firms are beginning to be more hes- itant about taking public stances that could anger us to help our clients navigate this in a thoughtful, practical and legally defensible way,\" said firm partner Jason Schwartz.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.33906947100063733,
      0.7266650751969443,
      0.4933078393881453,
      0.8046470915890825
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 52
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_31",
    "text": "sion in the workplace. Such initiatives have been under increasing fire since the Su- preme Court in 2023 ended affirmative action in higher education. Trump's election turns up the heat even more because he has campaigned against such initiatives.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17654557042702357,
      0.7273016630858598,
      0.32950924155513067,
      0.7852311609771624
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 53
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_26",
    "text": "The charged political envi- ronment is spurring specialty practice areas designed to help clients navigate it.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012109623964308477,
      0.7339858359194716,
      0.16507329509241556,
      0.7594493514760882
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 54
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_66",
    "text": "The latest proposal from Cintas, a maker of workplace products, was initially given to UniFirst's board in November.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6698534098151689,
      0.7463992997533222,
      0.9770554493307839,
      0.7597676454205459
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 55
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_27",
    "text": "Labor-law specialist firm Seyfarth Shaw created a cul- tural-flashpoints task force in 2023 to help clients navigate workplace challenges and re- spond to rising pressure for companies to take a stance on",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.7594493514760882,
      0.16379859783301465,
      0.8040105037001671
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 56
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_53",
    "text": "\"If law firms haven't in- vested in the regulatory space, it may be too late to recruit top talent,\" said Yvette Ostolaza, chair of Sid- ley Austin's management committee.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5047801147227533,
      0.7594493514760882,
      0.6577437858508605,
      0.8036922097557094
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 57
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_67",
    "text": "Cintas Bids For Rival UniFirst",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.6692160611854685,
      0.7654969364207846,
      0.8145315487571702,
      0.8202434948675101
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 58
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_72",
    "text": "recent investments in tech- nology and infrastructure.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8323773103887827,
      0.7658152303652423,
      0.9847036328871893,
      0.7785469881435506
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 59
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_71",
    "text": "Cintas also thinks inves- tors would like the deal: 79% of UniFirst common shares are held by investors who also own Cintas's stock, ac- cording to a Cintas analysis included in the letters deliv- ered to UniFirst's board.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8317399617590823,
      0.7782286941990929,
      0.9853409815168898,
      0.829155725312326
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 60
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_32",
    "text": "\"We're definitely seeing and anticipating increased de- mand and opportunities for social issues, said Lorie Almon, the firm's chair and managing partner.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17654557042702357,
      0.7849128670327047,
      0.3282345442957298,
      0.8040105037001671
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 61
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_40",
    "text": "Inside Robby Starbuck's Campaign To End DEl, One Company at a Time",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.05736137667304015,
      0.8154690857006446,
      0.2836201402166985,
      0.8310654889790722
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 62
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_43",
    "text": "Anthropic Value Hits $60 Billion",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.3403441682600382,
      0.8157873796451023,
      0.48502230720203954,
      0.8711705259807432
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 63
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_54",
    "text": "was a convertible note, mean- ing it will translate to equity at the valuation set in the cur- rent round.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5035054174633524,
      0.8164239675340177,
      0.65710643722116,
      0.8415691891461765
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 64
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_70",
    "text": "Continued from page B1 engage with UniFirst, includ- ing by stating its willingness to consider increasing its of- fer price, a subsequent letter says.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6692160611854685,
      0.829155725312326,
      0.8209050350541747,
      0.8673509986472507
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 65
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_74",
    "text": "A deal for UniFirst, should it happen, would be Cintas's biggest transaction yet.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8330146590184832,
      0.8294740192567837,
      0.9853409815168898,
      0.8482533619797883
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 66
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_41",
    "text": "- “ C",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.024219247928616953,
      0.8342484284236492,
      0.3186743148502231,
      0.9297366117609612
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 67
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_55",
    "text": "Anthropic develops and op- erates its technology in data centers operated by Amazon and Google, which also has in- vested billions of dollars in the startup. The startup's annual- ized revenue—an extrapolation of the next 12 months' revenue based on recent sales—re- cently hit about $875 million, one of the knowledgeable peo- ple said. Most of that has come from sales to busi- nesses.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5041427660930529,
      0.8422057770350919,
      0.6577437858508605,
      0.9303731996498766
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 68
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_73",
    "text": "Cintas is led by Chief Exec- utive Officer Todd Schneider, who has held that role since June 2021.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8323773103887827,
      0.8482533619797883,
      0.9847036328871893,
      0.8740351714808626
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 69
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_68",
    "text": "UniFirst has told Cintas that its board unanimously concluded that a deal wasn't in the best interest of the company and its stakeholders, according to correspondence in December and November. In October, UniFirst had said in a news release that it was excited about the invest- ments it was making and be- lieved its business had \"sig- nificant long-term potential.\"",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6679413639260675,
      0.867032704702793,
      0.8221797323135756,
      0.9504257181507122
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 70
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_44",
    "text": "Continued from page B1 lic stance in favor of robust safety testing for its technol- ogy out of concern AI could be misused or unintentionally cause catastrophic harm to hu- manity.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3403441682600382,
      0.880082756425559,
      0.49203314212874444,
      0.924643908649638
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 71
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_75",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "picture",
    "bbox": [
      0.8374760994263862,
      0.880082756425559,
      0.9847036328871893,
      0.9746160579294979
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 72
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_45",
    "text": "Much of Anthropic's fund- ing to date has come from its close partner Amazon.com, which committed $4 billion to the startup in November, bringing its total investment since 2023 to $8 billion. Ama- zon's November investment",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3403441682600382,
      0.9249622025940957,
      0.4926704907584449,
      0.975570939762871
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 73
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_56",
    "text": "OpenAI told investors when closing its October round that it expected to generate $3.7 billion in revenue last year, in large part from sales of the premium version of ChatGPT to consumers.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5041427660930529,
      0.931009787538792,
      0.6583811344805609,
      0.975570939762871
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 74
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_42",
    "text": "Scan this code for a video on conservative activist Robby Starbuck, who claims success for pushing public companies to change or abandon DEI and LGBTQ policies. WSJ looks at how he and his team do their work.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08986615678776291,
      0.9376939603724039,
      0.3161249203314213,
      0.9698416487626322
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018",
    "order": 75
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_018_69",
    "text": "For Cintas, a deal would allow the combined compa- nies to serve more customers and make greater use of its",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.668578712555768,
      0.9481976605395083,
      0.8215423836838751,
      0.975570939762871
    ],
